on php and a unix program called curl that can request web pages from the command line then use the service to schedule a job that uses curl to request cron php at regular intervals with the following command curl ss https www stanford edu dept example cgi bin drupal cron php the two flags ss tell curl to be silent unless there are errors support for assistance please submit a helpsu ticket rates free of charge getting started to get started first determine what command or script in afs you d like to run and then visit the scheduler's web interface at tools stanford edu cgi bin scheduler last modified tue 6 sep 2011 at 15 29 pages about this service overview actions scheduling service tool find answers submit a helpsu request stanford answers related pages afs at stanford cgi drupal on the stanford web service web infrastructure & resources footer links stanford university helpsu user login stanford university terms of use copyright complaints
